description.narrative: (Tanzania): RESPOND will reduce unmet needs for family planning (FP) by improving contraceptive choice; increasing education on, access to, and use of FP services, including before and after delivery; and integrating FP into other health areas, e.g., HIV, gender-based violence (GBV). It will cover 110 districts of Tanzania, reaching about seven million women of child-bearing age. It will support the Government of Tanzania goal of reducing maternal mortality and the U.S. Government development objective of improving broad-based socio-economic development, as stipulated in the Mission's new CDCS. Activities will include: providing FP through both static and outreach services; promoting new FP technologies; supporting post-abortion care clients; addressing GBV; and integrating FP into HIV services. Service provision will focus on rural, young, especially vulnerable and postpartum women. Expected results include serving over 761,000 clients with long-acting and permanent contraception and training over 1,600 service providers.
